<p>common equivalent shares</p>
<p>   outstanding		  10,673    9,299    10,635  10,184</p>
<p>NOTE: Applix Inc reported a charge of $10.8 million in 1996's fourth quarter for write-off of in-process technology for the Sinper Corp purchase. The company also reported a charge of $6.2 million related to the write-off of in-process technology for the Target Systems Corp purchase.</p>
<p>The fourth-quarter 1996 earnings before the charges were $2.2 million, or $0.21 a share, against $1.5 million, or $0.16 a share, for the same period the year before.</p>
<p>Before taking into account the charge in the fourth quarter for each respective period, net income for the year before the charges was $8.2 million, or $0.77 per share, versus comparable net income taxed at the current year's rates of $4.5 million or $0.44 per share. The company carried out a two-for-one stock split in December 1995.</p>
<p>-- New York Newsdesk 212 859-1610</p>
